FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS ABOUT INFOBOND

WHERE CAN I GET THEM PRINTED?
You can print the files at home on your own computer or take them to your local printer like WALMART PHOTO CENTER or STAPLES, or you may upload them to an online printing service: www.snapfish.com, www.shutterfly.com. To find places to print in your country, try a Google search including terms such as ‘Giclee Art Printing’ or ‘Poster Printing’ or ‘Photo Printing’ or ‘Online Printing’.
All of my prints have been tested to ensure you get the best quality. When having your prints done at your local photo print shop, if for any reason you don't feel the quality is good, please don't hesitate to ask them to do it again or even try a different paper.

WHAT PAPER SHOULD I PRINT MY ARTWORK ON?
The better quality paper you use the better quality print you will get.
Thick and ultra-thick paper or cardstock are some great options with a matte finish is great for a modern look and works really well with my artworks. But you might also like satin or gloss, it's really your personal preference.

CAN I PRINT IN LARGER SIZES?
It is no problem to print the A4 – A4 (8,3” x 11,7” or 21 x 29,7 cm) in a A3 (11,7" x 16,5" or 29,7 x 42 cm). It will still look good. You can go larger than that but the image will be more grainy. So if you don't mind a bit of grain you could try it.

Eclectic, odd and a bit cray cray, all my designs come from some of classic favourite films, songs, animals, quotes and other quirky inspirational paraphernalia. All my prints are created digitally.
